    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Making Life Choices</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Helen Maggie Carr letter on making choices in life with regard to making money (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''No Wealth of Opportunity,'' by Ann L. Berrios (Op-Ed, Sept. 25): It's irksome that some twentysomethings are getting all this good stuff, but they may be giving up something, too. If you choose to design Web sites to improve your income,  you will likely cut your chances of ever doing what you feel you're cut out to do.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''No Wealth of Opportunity,'' by Ann L. Berrios (Op-Ed, Sept. 25): It's irksome that some twentysomethings are getting all this good stuff, but they may be giving up something, too. If you choose to design Web sites to improve your income,  you will likely cut your chances of ever doing what you feel you're cut out to do.</p>
        <p>While those of us who choose the more uncertain path must be prepared to adjust our material expectations, I still wouldn't trade places with those who made the other choice.</p>
        <p>HELEN MAGGIE CARR  Glencliff, N.H., Sept. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
